Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.56,0:00:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reasoning and hints are interlinked,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.35,0:00:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allowing us to understand a case's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, the case gets resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.19,0:00:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will Conan catch the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.07,0:00:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.74,0:00:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.74,0:00:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.24,0:01:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji invited us to Osaka for the opening\Nparty of the World Restaurant, "K3".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.54,0:01:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restaurant owners were...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.42,0:01:54.13,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ricardo Barega\NFormer Boxer (36)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.42,0:01:53.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Former pro-boxer Ricardo Barega,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.38,0:01:57.51,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Mike Node\NMajor Leaguer (35)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Major Leaguer, Mike Node,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.80,0:02:00.97,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Ray Curtis\NPro Soccer Player (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.26,0:02:00.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,and pro-soccer star, Ray Curtis; those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, while those three were turning on lights, a gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.56,0:02:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gunshot rang out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.90,0:02:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An American reporter, Ed McKay,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,had been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:26.20,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Osaka "3 K's" Case
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:26.20,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.37,0:02:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, the case has ruined this party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.00,0:02:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now those three won't be able\Nto give out those signed goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you're lucky you got yours beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.05,0:02:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, where are Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.93,0:02:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, those two went off with Ohtaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r} for his investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.35,0:02:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Went off for his investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.40,0:02:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure everything'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police already have the pistol that was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, now Hattori Heiji's on the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hotel elevators won't be\Noperational until the hotel's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means those three...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.09,0:03:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could have only used the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.19,0:03:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the light switches seem to be installed and working.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:40.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the ones in these rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make it go on and off, you have\Nto push in the switch each time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.75,0:03:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told Mike to open the curtains...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you tied an open loop in a rope to the top of the\Ncurtain, you could do it from outside of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.01,0:04:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already looked through Mike's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to suggest anything was\Ntied to it or that it was tampered with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.65,0:04:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among those three, the most suspicious would\Nbe the one closest to the crime scene, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.91,0:04:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't have been him, because switching on the\Nlight and running up here takes at least ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray's left knee is injured, so there's\Nno way he'd make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Mike, he injured his arm in a previous game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ricardo's too big and slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, those three couldn't have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the past, you've always gone after suspects\Nuntil their alibi was proven beyond a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.99,0:05:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, making it to the door and knocking\Nwould take another five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It just can't be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.87,0:05:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Kudo, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.54,0:05:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a mop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They keep these in hotel rooms now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's a little weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo, couldn't it be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other two can't, but with what he uses so often,\Nhe could operate the light when he isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.07,0:05:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't have done it. No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.86,0:05:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiding such a small tool with so many\Npeople around would be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.16,0:05:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be done!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.83,0:05:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll prove it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:05:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.00,0:06:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:10.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,When you have eliminated the\Nimpossible, whatever remains,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:13.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,however improbable, must be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.68,0:06:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it's hard to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what you always say, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, my old injury... It still bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.95,0:06:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm OK. If I take some medicine, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rust on an iron fortress will make it worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's tryin' to drop or somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this time I can't be wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.48,0:07:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it in the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, your dad's saying stupid stuff again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The employee was shocked as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.74,0:07:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He understood what I meant by "bandou", too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.87,0:07:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Ed guy that died was very familiar with Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to a sushi stand nearby for clues and found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.18,0:07:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.93,0:07:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can this be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this deflated soccer ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over here's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's an extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.95,0:07:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.03,0:07:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, can we head back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These two want to head back to the hotel for a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.83,0:08:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let them go, Ohtaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The test didn't show anything on those three anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.38,0:08:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there is one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind doing one thing for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want me to do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.10,0:08:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll let you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.73,0:08:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, someone is waiting for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.37,0:08:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the hotel room you're staying in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This request is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.37,0:08:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For your biggest fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.50,0:08:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, gosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.68,0:08:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:08:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.51,0:09:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the same simple method.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, right before the door automatically locks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.06,0:09:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You take a mop from the closet and remove the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.53,0:09:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put the door near the switch and put\Nthe end of the mop between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then make sure the mop's angle allows\Nthe door to lean against the switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Preparation complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you get the soccer ball you prepared earlier and kick it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You opened the curtain when you first came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it to make sure that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:53.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We would see the trick the second it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.70,0:09:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.41,0:09:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.83,0:10:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After practicing a few times, even a kid like me can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were once middle fielder Ray Curtis,\Nknown for his powerful free-kicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.63,0:10:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would be nothing for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, by doing this, you can switch the light on the\Nfirst floor off while you're on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time, you could shoot the reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would give you an air-tight alibi\Nthat no one would challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.40,0:10:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, little boy, don't joke around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to go into more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.91,0:10:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were responsible for the five lights...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the first two floors of the "K".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room you used this trick on was #2,\Nthe one on the far left of the 1st floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:10:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, it's the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Facing the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.76,0:11:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you turned on the light in the first room,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you moved to the second room to prepare the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also took the soccer ball and\Ngun you had prepared earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.77,0:11:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then turned on the lights in rooms #3, #4, and #5.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, you left out the second room on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Ran, who was outside of the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.79,0:11:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,noticed that you hadn't turned on #2's light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you'd go over the transceiver, giving you time\Nto run to the soccer ball and kick it down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This completed the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.59,0:11:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.89,0:11:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You went and shot Ed, who was waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then threw the gun inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.06,0:11:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you ran down to room #2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:12:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pretended you'd been there the entire time, and that\Nyou were as shocked by the gunshot as everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that how it happened, Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, very, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, little boy, you forgot something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.25,0:12:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran said there were only three seconds\Nbetween the shot and my light coming on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have done all of this in time, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did I kick the ball, run to Ed's room and knock, and\Nwait for him to open the door all in three seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't kick and then knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knocked and then kicked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.73,0:12:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After knocking on Ed's door, you ran to the ball\Nand kicked it right when he opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.70,0:12:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were still talking to Ran on the\Ntransceiver at the time as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you, doing this in three seconds is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:13:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's possible that Ricardo could tie a string\Nto a mop and do this trick on the 5th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the crime scene is on the second floor, your floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't be able to run from the 2nd\Nfloor to the 5th in three seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.73,0:13:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, Mike looked perfectly fine\Nwhen he opened the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:23.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, boy, what about the gun powder?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the police were checking for it, they\Nonly tested the outside of your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't get to check inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You removed your jacket before the crime and\Nturned your shirt and pants inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before you went back to the window to\Nlook out, you put your jacket back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.89,0:13:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would've noticed from that far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.89,0:14:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, you used this pin to deflate the\Nsoccerball and hide it under your shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this in the trash can in the toilet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the party reception, none of the balls were deflated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.04,0:14:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, where's your proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.33,0:14:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Ed who told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.34,0:14:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ed's three fingers referred to how Japanese people eat sushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while his left hand gripping his belt meant to say "bandou".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In sushi restaurants, the staff tries to\Navoid giving out prices until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:44.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They use secret signals, like "bandou" for item #8.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.69,0:14:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also the number his killer, Ray Curtis, wears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was his dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the towel in your room is still wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.63,0:15:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used it to clean off the powder, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, water will help you pass the powder test.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.18,0:15:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.73,0:15:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to prove you innocent, so I started to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.11,0:15:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the further along I got, more came up pointing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.78,0:15:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Little boy, how unfortunate that all\Nyou've said isn't enough to convict me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My shirt and pants that I wore earlier\Nare in the hands of the cleaners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I changed because I sweat a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure they're being washed in the\Nlaundry room of this hotel right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about your shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.05,0:15:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.97,0:16:03.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For semi-automatic guns, the gun\Npowder comes out of the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for revolvers, the gun powder\Nemits from the body of the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it'd be on your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.74,0:16:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray, you were wearing shoes when you did it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be able to kick it accurately otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether or not you changed and cleaned your shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'll be the deciding evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.26,0:16:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.43,0:16:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please just give up, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:16:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's something I can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I were to get arrested, my fans, my\Nfamily, they'd be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.04,0:17:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for telling me about my shoes,\Nboy, I'll go clean them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've helped me beat the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.25,0:17:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That isn't your only problem right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Iron Wall of Europe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray Curtis!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How good are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How good are you really, Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was only a high school student's kick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should've been able to block it with one hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.51,0:17:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Answer me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.84,0:18:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Answer me, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.31,0:18:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I use drugs, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.77,0:18:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recurring yawning and joint pains\Nare both symptoms of drug abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.07,0:18:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed when you were coming out of the toilet\Nearlier that your knee is still giving you trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you take them to stop the pains\Nin your muscles and in your joints.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I should've known, that super-play...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it isn't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started after he wrote that false rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard Ed's lies caused my wife to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.78,0:19:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He followed me all the way over here\Nto Japan, to my wife's hometown...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In Pursuit of Ray's Drug Abuse: On Site in Japan."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.21,0:19:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, my wife decided she couldn't\Ntake it anymore and left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.05,0:19:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I started...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.77,0:19:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you are facing a bitter aspect of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drugs and murder are foul, without any excuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deserve a red card, for a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True, I was a cheater.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bad player, and I lost the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must be ejected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For both my late wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.30,0:20:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for a fan like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ray then admitted to the crime and\Nwas taken away by the Osaka Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goalkeeper who wore #8...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.49,0:20:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disappeared from the field, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.55,0:22:08.30,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Heiji's Home
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.39,0:22:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did that boy really say he wasn't\Ngoing to watch the match in Nagai?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.60,0:22:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.86,0:22:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was looking forward to it so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be because Ray won't be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.61,0:22:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, there will be many other\Nfamous soccer players there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.41,0:22:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he was going to see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.70,0:22:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s face right now is just like Shinichi's.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.33,0:22:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everytime Shinichi would lose something he\Nliked, he'd just have this sad, child-like face.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.13,0:22:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} be... They both like soccer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.14,0:22:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.14,0:23:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deserve to be hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.65,0:23:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.61,0:23:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.03,0:23:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.22,0:23:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's in a better mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two look just like brothers, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.10,0:23:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so?
